solution.p:
Setting the frequency equal to 1046.5, we can solve for x: 
            1046.5 \amp= 440(2)^{x/12}
            \frac{1046.5}{440} \amp= 2^{x/12}
            \ln\left(\frac{1046.5}{440}\right) \amp= \frac{x}{12}\ln(2)
            x \amp= \frac{12}{\ln(2)}\ln\left(\frac{1046.5}{440}\right)
            \amp \approx 15

Because she rejected  people, we solve the equation:

                \text{Rejected} \amp= \frac{\text{Total}}{e}
                 \amp= \frac{\text{Total}}{e}
                \text{Total} \amp= e
                \amp\approx

statement.p:
Suppose a population is given by

                P(t) = e^{t}

              where t is measured in years from now. Determine when the population doubles.

Suppose a value is decaying, and \% remains after 1000 years. The amount of the substance can be modeled by the function

  f(t) = Ae^{kt}

where A is the initial amount, t is the number of years, and the constant k is the continuous rate of decay. Find the value of k.

